Author: Gardner, Martin, 1914-2010.
Subtitle: The Wild Adventures of Dorothy, the Scarecrow, and the Tin Woodman
GoodreadsDes: Dorothy and friends return in this Oz sequel, this time to New York City, on the eve of the 100th anniversary of "The Wizard of Oz". Combining mathematical riddles with technological pyrotechnics and vivid suspense, Martin Gardner has created a new fable celebrating the power of imagination and the lure of an ageless heroine named Dorothy from the turn of the century.

Title: A burden of earth and other stories
Author: Bosworth, Beth, 1957-
TitleClean: A Burden of Earth and Other Stories
GoodreadsDes: "Beth Bosworth sets her stories in the labyrinth of family life, bravely exploring its dark turns and heartstopping entanglements. The minds of her characters are self haunted with their memories, and what is imagined as the past is as crucially immediate as the present. A BURDEN OF EARTH is the debut of a gifted writer--someone to watch"--E. L. Doctorow.

Title: Stripping, and other stories
Author: Kennedy, Pagan, 1962-
Subtitle: and other stories
GoodreadsDes: Stripping is a collection of stories about female misfits - punk teenagers, voodoo queens, math. nerds, sickly little girls - each coping with the limits of her life by making up an elaborate and flattering lie about herself, a fantastic tale in which she escapes her helpless situation.
Subjects: Young women United States Social life and customs Fiction

Title: A disturbance in one place : a novel
Author: Kirshenbaum, Binnie
GoodreadsDes: Brazen and given to transgressions, the narrator of this mordantly witty novel is an aloof, tough talking, married Manhattan woman who carries on three affairs simultaneously, blithely breaking seven of the Ten Commandments in her search for a safe place to land. Rootless, bouncing from bed to bed, she knows she is pure of heart.
